properties.name: tilebuilder.debug.enabled
properties.description: Enable TileBuilder debugging. When debugging is enabled, several other debugging options can take effect and will change certain aspects of TileBuilder like the rendering of tiles and caching behaviour.

properties.name: tilebuilder.debug.tile.bounds
properties.description: When enabled, a 1 pixel border will be rendered around (but inside) each tile. This option needs tilebuilder.debug.enabled to be true.

properties.name: tilebuilder.debug.tile.overlap
properties.description: When enabled, areas within a tile that are not actually occupied by image data will be highlighted. This option needs tilebuilder.debug.enabled to be true.
